==Latin==
===Idiom===
'''ad kalendas Graecas'''
#never.

'''Notes''': Attributed by [[w:Suetonius|Suetonius]] in ''[[w:Lives of the Twelve Caesars|Lives of the Twelve Caesars]]'' to [[w:Caesar Augustus|Caesar Augustus]]. The phrase means "never" and is similar to phrases like "[[when pigs fly]]". The [[Kalends]] (also written ''[[Calends]]'') were specific days of the [[w:Roman calendar|Roman calendar]], not of the [[w:Attic calendar|Greek]], and so the "Greek Kalends" would never occur.

====Translations====
*French: [[aux calendes grecques]]

